# MkDocs Site

## Public URLs

| Section | Path |
|---------|------|
| Root redirect | `/` → `/en/` |
| English | `/en/` |
| Persian | `/fa/` |
| Chinese | `/zh/` |
| Cheatsheet (EN) | `/en/cheatsheet/` |

Live: `http://blog.ceph-s3.ir/` · `site_url` in `mkdocs.yml` must match.

## docs/ layout (symlinks)

```
docs/
├── index.md              # root hub (hand-written HTML)
├── cheatsheet/ → ../cheatsheet   # cli, config, guides, index, OVERVIEW
├── arch/ → ../arch
└── dev/ → ../dev
```

Rebuild symlinks after clone or layout changes:

```bash
python3 scripts/setup-docs-layout.py
```

## Section homepages (do not overwrite)

| Source | Served as |
|--------|-----------|
| `cheatsheet/index.md` (+ `.fa.md`, `.zh.md`) | `/cheatsheet/` |
| `arch/index.md` (+ fa/zh) | `/arch/` |
| `dev/index.md` (+ fa/zh) | `/dev/` |

`sync-docs-index.py` syncs **only** `cheatsheet/OVERVIEW.md`, `docs/version.md`, `docs/license.md` — **never** section `index.md` files.

Hub pages use `hub-page--{cheatsheet|arch|dev}` classes, `docs/stylesheets/hub.css`, `docs/javascripts/hub.js`. Locale links use **site-root absolute** paths (`/fa/cheatsheet/`, not `../fa/`).

## Build & CI

```bash
python3 scripts/regenerate-docs.py   # includes mkdocs build + restructure
python3 scripts/restructure-site-locales.py   # after mkdocs build alone
python3 scripts/validate-docs-paths.py
mkdocs serve   # dev preview (English still at / until restructure)
```

CI (`.github/workflows/docs.yml`): `setup-docs-layout` → generators → `fix-html-hrefs` → `validate-docs-paths` → `mkdocs build`.

## Do not

- Commit real files under `docs/cheatsheet/{cli,config,guides}` — use symlinks
- Edit `docs/index.md` by running old sync that copied REFERENCE wholesale
- Break nav paths in `mkdocs.yml` without running `validate-docs-paths.py`
